                          <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-slate-700">{row.duration}</td>
                          <td class="px-4 py-2.5 font-mono font-semibold text-forest-700">{row.approxFare}</td>
                          <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-slate-600 text-xs">{row.frequency}</td>
                        </tr>
                      ))}
                    </tbody>
                  </table>
                </div>
                <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
                  CP (Comboios de Portugal) Minho line. Check current times at cp.pt. Weekend and holiday schedules differ significantly from weekday service.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3 text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">Step-by-Step: Overland Caminha → Tui</h4>
                <ol class="space-y-2 text-xs text-amber-900">
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">1.</span> Walk from town centre to Caminha railway station (~5 min, 400m south of the main square).</li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">2.</span> Buy a ticket to Valença at the station window or vending machine (~€3.60). Check departure time.</li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">3.</span> Train journey Caminha → Valença: ~35 minutes. Scenic journey along the Minho valley.</li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">4.</span> From Valença station, walk north through the medieval walled city (~20 min) to reach the international bridge.</li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">5.</span> Cross the <strong>Ponte Internacional Valença–Tui</strong> on foot (~1.5 km, ~20 min). The bridge has a dedicated pedestrian path.</li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">6.</span> You arrive in <strong>Tui</strong> (Spain). Currency stays euros. The Camino Portugués Interior yellow arrows begin immediately from the bridge entrance.</li>
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5"><span class="font-bold shrink-0 w-4">7.</span> Get your credential stamped at Tui Cathedral or the Albergue Buen Camino before continuing north.</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
